<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-16T03:12:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-16T03:12:00-05:00" n="187" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13238: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, United States Asiatic
                                    Fleet</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of
                                    Naval Operations</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)<note n="61" xml:id="d187fn61">Copy
                                    of telegram transmitted to the Department by the Navy
                                    Department.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-16T16:12:00+08:00">June 16, 1938—4:12
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 16—12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>0016. Japanese source states that unless Chinese initiate peace talks
                                soon after fall Hankow Japs intend renew drive against armies at <pb facs="0202" n="198" xml:id="pg_198"/> once not repeating mistake
                                of waiting allowing Chinese to recover as after fall Nanking.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>